thread.title: Rafael Nadal Exits With Leg Injury at the Australian Open

author: Tom Perrotta
title: Rafael Nadal Exits With Leg Injury at the Australian Open
text:
Two games after playing four strenuous sets, Rafael Nadal retired from his Australian Open quarterfinal match on Tuesday night with an injury.
Nadal led Marin Cilic by two sets to one but began to struggle in the middle of the fourth set and took a medical timeout. The injury, in his upper right leg, was massaged but not cured. By the time the fifth set began, he couldnâ€™t move without pain.
